- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the structure of different voting systems and analyzes their drawbacks, which falls under the domain of data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses the social implications of voting systems and how they can be improved to ensure transparency and privacy, which falls under the domain of computers and society. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a new approach to voting systems based on blockchain technology, which falls under the domain of software engineering.
